Key Match Events: Ben Stokes scored 108 runs off 84 balls.
The Netherlands was all out for 179, chasing 340 for victory.
Adil Rashid claimed 3-54, while Moeen Ali bagged 3-42.
Dawid Malan scored 87 runs and Chris Woakes scored 51 runs.
England amassed a total of 9-339 in 50 overs.
Post-Match Reflections: Ben Stokes expressed his pleasure in getting a victory and mentioned it was a tough World Cup.
Stokes commented on the pitch conditions, describing it as a nice wicket to bat on with a bit of tennis-ball bounce.
Miscellaneous Highlights: England snapped its five-match losing streak at the men's Cricket World Cup.
The win lifted England to seventh place in the 10-team standings with four points.
The Netherlands dropped to 10th place but is still in the hunt for a Champions Trophy spot.
